Dialogue: 9,0:02:30.93,0:02:33.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who rejected Nakajou's theory?
Dialogue: 9,0:02:34.54,0:02:35.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me.
Dialogue: 9,0:02:35.38,0:02:38.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Haba's and Sawakiguchi's, too?
Dialogue: 9,0:02:38.01,0:02:38.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 9,0:02:39.31,0:02:45.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I first asked you to solve this mystery, you said not to expect too much from you.
Dialogue: 9,0:02:45.75,0:02:49.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you rejected and buried each of their theories.
Dialogue: 9,0:02:49.52,0:02:51.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I expected you to.
Dialogue: 9,0:02:51.90,0:02:53.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as you expected?
Dialogue: 9,0:02:53.79,0:02:55.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They weren't of the right caliber.
Dialogue: 9,0:02:55.99,0:03:01.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew from the start that they didn't have what it took to solve the case.
Dialogue: 9,0:03:01.29,0:03:03.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that was just a farce? Then—
Dialogue: 9,0:03:03.13,0:03:06.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I won't say they are incompetent.
Dialogue: 9,0:03:06.04,0:03:07.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They each have their own unique talents.
Dialogue: 9,0:03:07.66,0:03:12.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, that does not mean that they are of use in this situation.
Dialogue: 9,0:03:12.14,0:03:12.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then—
Dialogue: 9,0:03:12.56,0:03:14.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you...
Dialogue: 9,0:03:14.25,0:03:19.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you weren't helping us, we would have chosen one of their ideas,
Dialogue: 9,0:03:19.64,0:03:22.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the project would probably have ended in failure.
Dialogue: 9,0:03:23.96,0:03:25.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're quite frank, aren't you?
Dialogue: 9,0:03:25.42,0:03:26.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brutally so.
Dialogue: 9,0:03:26.59,0:03:28.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I must be, I will be.
Dialogue: 9,0:03:28.18,0:03:31.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, there is one person I can count on.
Dialogue: 9,0:03:32.57,0:03:36.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard about this individual from three people.
Dialogue: 9,0:03:36.60,0:03:38.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The first was Chitanda Eru.
Dialogue: 9,0:03:38.20,0:03:40.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The second was someone outside the school.
Dialogue: 9,0:03:40.10,0:03:42.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And last was Tougaito Masashi.
Dialogue: 9,0:03:42.77,0:03:48.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believed that this person could be our detective for this movie.
Dialogue: 9,0:03:48.45,0:03:50.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was you I wanted from the start.
Dialogue: 9,0:03:50.72,0:03:51.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not the Classics Club.
Dialogue: 9,0:03:55.50,0:03:56.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-kun.
Dialogue: 9,0:03:57.28,0:04:02.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe that your work thus far has clearly demonstrated your own talents.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:03.09,0:04:05.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are special.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:14.54,0:04:16.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are special.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:18.45,0:04:20.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so, I'd like to ask you again.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:20.70,0:04:24.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-kun, please lend your assistance to class 2-F.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:24.79,0:04:27.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please find the true answer to that video.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:28.81,0:04:30.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have any talents or anything.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:30.85,0:04:32.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was just lucky.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:34.37,0:04:35.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How irritating.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:36.40,0:04:38.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me tell you a story.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:38.39,0:04:40.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Think of it as a little entertainment.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:40.67,0:04:43.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once upon a time, there was a bench member in a sports club.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:44.94,0:04:49.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This member practiced every day to become part of the regular team,
Dialogue: 9,0:04:49.10,0:04:51.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but no matter how hard she tried, she couldn't make it,
Dialogue: 9,0:04:51.00,0:04:56.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because there were more talented members in the club than her.
Dialogue: 9,0:04:56.48,0:05:00.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And among them, there was one who could even be called a prodigy.
Dialogue: 9,0:05:00.15,0:05:04.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, the difference between the bench and the prodigy was like that between heaven and earth.
Dialogue: 9,0:05:04.82,0:05:10.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At one competition, the prodigy was named MVP for her invaluability to the team.
Dialogue: 9,0:05:10.37,0:05:12.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An interviewer asked her,
Dialogue: 9,0:05:12.62,0:05:16.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"You were amazing today. What's your secret?"
Dialogue: 9,0:05:16.24,0:05:18.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She answered,
Dialogue: 9,0:05:18.50,0:05:21.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I was just lucky."
Dialogue: 9,0:05:22.96,0:05:27.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How deeply do you think this answer cut into the heart of the bench member?
Dialogue: 9,0:05:28.06,0:05:29.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 9,0:05:32.77,0:05:35.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Every individual must be aware of themselves.
Dialogue: 9,0:05:35.71,0:05:39.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If not, those who watch them think fools of themselves.
Dialogue: 9,0:05:42.45,0:05:45.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I... special?
Dialogue: 9,0:05:46.25,0:05:50.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do I see myself as I really am?
Dialogue: 9,0:05:52.00,0:05:54.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I believe her?
Dialogue: 9,0:06:06.45,0:06:08.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Irisu-senpai, I...
Dialogue: 9,0:06:10.66,0:06:12.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now this is rare.
Dialogue: 9,0:06:12.09,0:06:15.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Houtarou voluntarily going to school on a holiday?
Dialogue: 9,0:06:16.49,0:06:17.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have something to do?
Dialogue: 9,0:06:17.61,0:06:20.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do I need something to do to go to school?
Dialogue: 9,0:06:20.94,0:06:23.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, but it's not in your character.
Dialogue: 9,0:06:23.64,0:06:26.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Irisu-senpai gave me direct orders.
Dialogue: 9,0:06:26.54,0:06:28.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to find out who killed Kaitou.
Dialogue: 9,0:06:29.53,0:06:30.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 9,0:06:30.49,0:06:31.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to?
Dialogue: 9,0:06:31.20,0:06:34.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki Houtarou is a passionate and honorable man.
Dialogue: 9,0:06:34.66,0:06:36.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think I heard that right.
Dialogue: 9,0:06:36.25,0:06:36.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say that again?
Dialogue: 9,0:06:38.40,0:06:41.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's quite a change from your motto.
Dialogue: 9,0:06:41.25,0:06:43.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did Chitanda-san convert you?
Dialogue: 9,0:06:43.22,0:06:43.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 9,0:06:43.79,0:06:46.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why?
Dialogue: 9,0:06:46.01,0:06:47.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"If I don't have to do it, I won't."
Dialogue: 9,0:06:48.78,0:06:50.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that your motto?
Dialogue: 9,0:06:53.39,0:06:54.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satoshi.
Dialogue: 9,0:07:00.72,0:07:04.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think there's something that only you can do?
Dialogue: 9,0:07:08.12,0:07:08.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not really.
Dialogue: 9,0:07:09.55,0:07:09.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No?
Dialogue: 9,0:07:10.51,0:07:12.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't I tell you?
Dialogue: 9,0:07:12.11,0:07:13.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a man of no talents.
Dialogue: 9,0:07:14.20,0:07:17.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For example, I might long to be a Sherlockian,
Dialogue: 9,0:07:17.74,0:07:20.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I will never be one.
Dialogue: 9,0:07:20.77,0:07:27.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The fundamental reason is that I lack the gall to dive into the depths of the labyrinths of wisdom.
Dialogue: 9,0:07:28.55,0:07:32.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If Mayaka were to find an interest in Holmes, I guarantee you,
Dialogue: 9,0:07:33.43,0:07:35.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she'd be better than me in three months.
Dialogue: 9,0:07:36.32,0:07:43.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exploring the gateways of multiple genres and getting a stamp on the pamphlet is the best I can do.
Dialogue: 9,0:07:43.71,0:07:45.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never be the lead.
Dialogue: 9,0:07:46.94,0:07:48.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know why you're asking.
Dialogue: 9,0:07:48.70,0:07:50.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Irisu-senpai got you worked up.
Dialogue: 9,0:07:51.78,0:07:56.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That would explain why you're suddenly doubting your own character.
Dialogue: 9,0:07:56.46,0:07:59.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you don't doubt your own?
Dialogue: 9,0:07:59.49,0:08:00.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, yeah.
Dialogue: 9,0:08:01.29,0:08:02.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going on ahead.
Dialogue: 9,0:08:02.83,0:08:05.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayaka should be there today.
Dialogue: 9,0:08:05.30,0:08:06.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go say hi.
Dialogue: 9,0:08:06.29,0:08:07.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satoshi.
Dialogue: 9,0:08:08.00,0:08:13.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what you really think of yourself, but I have a higher opinion of you than what you said.
Dialogue: 9,0:08:13.67,0:08:19.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think you can become one of the best Sherlockians in Japan if you tried.
Dialogue: 9,0:08:23.30,0:08:26.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are things I'm more interested in than being a Sherlockian.
Dialogue: 9,0:08:28.50,0:08:29.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though...
Dialogue: 9,0:08:31.45,0:08:32.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am jealous.
Dialogue: 9,0:08:33.75,0:08:34.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly.
Dialogue: 9,0:08:40.34,0:08:44.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's summer break and Oreki came to school of his own accord?!
Dialogue: 9,0:08:44.91,0:08:46.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there something wrong with me coming?
Dialogue: 9,0:08:46.41,0:08:47.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course!
Dialogue: 9,0:08:47.62,0:08:50.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like the calm before the storm of the century...
Dialogue: 9,0:08:51.84,0:08:53.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I felt like solving a mystery.
Dialogue: 9,0:08:53.60,0:08:55.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You? Why?
Dialogue: 9,0:08:58.38,0:09:00.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet Irisu-senpai got you worked up somehow.
Dialogue: 9,0:09:02.01,0:09:03.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're pretty sharp, Mayaka.
Dialogue: 9,0:09:04.45,0:09:06.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever.
Dialogue: 9,0:09:06.07,0:09:08.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened after we went home?
Dialogue: 9,0:09:08.62,0:09:09.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To Chii-chan?
Dialogue: 9,0:09:09.95,0:09:12.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like she got home just fine.
Dialogue: 9,0:09:12.16,0:09:15.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I called her this morning though, she was still in bed with a hangover.
Dialogue: 9,0:09:15.03,0:09:18.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a pretty rare case...
Dialogue: 9,0:09:19.67,0:09:23.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, either way, let's have another look at the movie.
Dialogue: 9,0:09:27.48,0:09:28.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaitou!
Dialogue: 9,0:09:33.15,0:09:34.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-Blood!
Dialogue: 9,0:09:38.86,0:09:41.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What's that?
Dialogue: 9,0:09:43.43,0:09:46.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaitou-senpai's severed arm is really good.
Dialogue: 9,0:09:46.76,0:09:48.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like a real arm.
Dialogue: 9,0:09:48.53,0:09:52.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe the most talented in that class was the props master.
Dialogue: 9,0:09:54.69,0:09:56.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way...
Dialogue: 9,0:09:58.64,0:10:02.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I still can't see where there'd be any major tricks...
Dialogue: 9,0:10:02.24,0:10:03.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 9,0:10:03.01,0:10:05.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're making something hard look really simple.
Dialogue: 9,0:10:05.77,0:10:07.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 9,0:10:07.50,0:10:11.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This doesn't look simple because it was made to be simple.
Dialogue: 9,0:10:11.16,0:10:12.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why?
Dialogue: 9,0:10:12.96,0:10:21.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think the mystery isn't coming to light because it's boring as a movie, and so the viewer can't get into it.
Dialogue: 9,0:10:22.05,0:10:29.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Several volunteers from class 2-F decided to produce an exhibit on the history of Narakubo at the Kanya Festival. {timing check}
Dialogue: 9,0:10:25.90,0:10:27.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 9,0:10:27.34,0:10:32.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't even realize that it would be a locked room mystery until well into the movie.
Dialogue: 9,0:10:32.60,0:10:35.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not very good at presenting itself as one.
Dialogue: 9,0:10:35.47,0:10:36.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like how?
Dialogue: 9,0:10:36.64,0:10:38.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The camera work is horrible.
Dialogue: 9,0:10:38.17,0:10:39.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! That's why!
Dialogue: 9,0:10:39.55,0:10:42.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then how would you film it?
Dialogue: 9,0:10:42.11,0:10:43.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me?
Dialogue: 9,0:10:44.43,0:10:45.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 9,0:10:45.80,0:10:48.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For example...
Dialogue: 9,0:10:48.37,0:10:49.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This scene.
Dialogue: 9,0:10:50.65,0:10:56.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would be better to use an angle and distance that shows both the characters and interior.
Dialogue: 9,0:10:56.90,0:10:58.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 9,0:10:58.34,0:11:00.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 9,0:11:00.07,0:11:00.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:00.87,0:11:02.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Sugimura!
Dialogue: 9,0:11:02.51,0:11:03.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Find anything?
Dialogue: 9,0:11:04.34,0:11:07.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mine was fairly clean. We might be able to use it.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:07.45,0:11:13.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\q2}If they shot this from Sugimura's point of view, it would \Nbe easier to tell that the lobby was visible from his location.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:13.95,0:11:18.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the camera looks up from the lobby, the viewer can't know that.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:18.25,0:11:19.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 9,0:11:19.61,0:11:21.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 9,0:11:21.12,0:11:23.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think that's enough.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:23.17,0:11:24.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 9,0:11:24.40,0:11:25.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no end to it.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:26.23,0:11:28.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just criticizing the video won't get us anywhere.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:29.23,0:11:32.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come now. It might be a good idea to go through it.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:33.89,0:11:35.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I found you, Fukube!
Dialogue: 9,0:11:37.21,0:11:39.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you're playing around in a place like this?
Dialogue: 9,0:11:39.30,0:11:40.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey there, Yamauchi-kun! Welcome.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:40.95,0:11:43.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, could you not get violent?
Dialogue: 9,0:11:43.90,0:11:45.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm doing this for your sake!
Dialogue: 9,0:11:45.85,0:11:48.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I have things that I have to—
Dialogue: 9,0:11:48.72,0:11:49.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be stupid!
Dialogue: 9,0:11:49.64,0:11:51.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Omichi is serious!
Dialogue: 9,0:11:51.00,0:11:53.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're staying back a year if you don't go!
Dialogue: 9,0:11:54.00,0:11:56.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satoshi, you should probably go take those make-up tests.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:56.85,0:12:00.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But Hongou-senpai's mystery is really important!
Dialogue: 9,0:12:00.60,0:12:03.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Houtarou, could you do a little solving right about now?
Dialogue: 9,0:12:03.35,0:12:05.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the heck are you talking about?
Dialogue: 9,0:12:05.41,0:12:06.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you see—
Dialogue: 9,0:12:07.90,0:12:09.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 9,0:12:09.38,0:12:10.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to know the secret!
Dialogue: 9,0:12:10.96,0:12:12.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The locked room!
Dialogue: 9,0:12:13.31,0:12:14.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's gone.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:14.65,0:12:16.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is he stupid?
Dialogue: 9,0:12:17.20,0:12:18.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's back.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:18.55,0:12:20.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Houtarou.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:20.80,0:12:22.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't escape from the long arm of the law.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:23.80,0:12:27.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since it's come to this, think of this notebook as me.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:24.80,0:12:25.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fukube!
Dialogue: 9,0:12:27.75,0:12:29.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, let's go!
Dialogue: 9,0:12:29.01,0:12:31.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, okay! I'm going!
Dialogue: 9,0:12:31.22,0:12:32.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez...
Dialogue: 9,0:12:32.75,0:12:33.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright...
Dialogue: 9,0:12:33.95,0:12:35.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I should get going, too.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:35.59,0:12:36.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 9,0:12:37.11,0:12:38.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with that look?
Dialogue: 9,0:12:38.85,0:12:43.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I might want to help Irisu-senpai, but I have no intention of helping {\i1}you{\i0}.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:43.29,0:12:43.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that so.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:43.90,0:12:45.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the librarian today.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:45.60,0:12:50.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I knew we were going to do this, I would have taken today off.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:50.01,0:12:52.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's your fault for not telling me beforehand.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:53.79,0:12:54.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still...
Dialogue: 9,0:12:55.65,0:12:57.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about this, Oreki.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:06.40,0:13:07.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then...
Dialogue: 9,0:13:08.41,0:13:10.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's split up and look around inside.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:11.93,0:13:14.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn, who would do this?!
Dialogue: 9,0:13:14.02,0:13:15.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-Blood!
Dialogue: 9,0:13:16.58,0:13:18.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That won't be a problem.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:18.31,0:13:20.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They should be here.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:42.06,0:13:42.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:49.47,0:13:52.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's what Hongou was going for.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:52.97,0:13:54.56,Staff Room,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an5\pos(638.286,348.704)\fad(0,150)\be1\c&H091116&\b0\fs25\fscx150\fscy150\3c&H0E1423&\i0}Shosho
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.97,0:13:54.56,Staff Room,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an5\pos(637.333,349.275)\fad(0,150)\fn\be1\bord1\fs25\c&H091116&\b0\fscx150\fscy150\3c&H0E1423&}Shosho
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.97,0:13:56.02,Staff Room,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\be1\c&H07070C&\fs25\b1\pos(228.457,565.791)}When the sun's heat fades\Nand first gives way to the cool air.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.52,0:13:56.02,Episode Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an5\pos(636,348.59)\fad(250,0)\bord1\blur3\b1\c&H030004&\fscx151\fscy156\3c&H777687&}Hyouka
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.52,0:13:56.02,Episode Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an5\pos(636,349.733)\fad(250,0)\b1\c&H030004&\fscx151\fscy156}Hyouka
Dialogue: 9,0:13:58.73,0:13:59.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come in.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:05.50,0:14:06.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, let me ask:
Dialogue: 9,0:14:06.82,0:14:08.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you figure it out?
Dialogue: 9,0:14:10.53,0:14:12.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Go ahead.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:12.45,0:14:13.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:14.32,0:14:18.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It goes without saying that the key to this puzzle is the locked room.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:18.64,0:14:19.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaitou—
Dialogue: 9,0:14:19.51,0:14:24.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, no one could have entered the room where Kaitou-senpai died,
Dialogue: 9,0:14:24.91,0:14:26.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,nor could they have left it.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:26.71,0:14:28.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can just use their screen names.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:30.70,0:14:32.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stage Left was a locked room.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:32.51,0:14:34.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn, who would do this?!
Dialogue: 9,0:14:36.60,0:14:39.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only window leading outside was clearly unusable.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:40.65,0:14:44.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means that the only remaining possibility is that the culprit used the door.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:44.90,0:14:46.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But how?
Dialogue: 9,0:14:47.57,0:14:51.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From the video, we cannot say for sure whether there's some physical trick regarding that door,
Dialogue: 9,0:14:51.17,0:14:56.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so the most reasonable assumption is that the culprit used the master key to get in.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:56.55,0:14:59.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, Sugimura would have seen everything in the lobby.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:59.73,0:15:03.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Additionally, the right hand corridor was the only way to get to the room.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:03.69,0:15:05.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the second locked room puzzle.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:05.88,0:15:12.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\q2}None of those six members would have been able to enter the \Noffice, get the key, and then get to the right hand corridor unseen.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:12.64,0:15:14.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does this imply?
Dialogue: 9,0:15:15.47,0:15:18.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we assume that none of those six were the culprit, then that leaves only one possibility:
Dialogue: 9,0:15:19.29,0:15:22.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was a seventh person there.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:22.79,0:15:24.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A seventh?
Dialogue: 9,0:15:24.17,0:15:25.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like Sawakiguchi's theory?
Dialogue: 9,0:15:25.57,0:15:26.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:26.83,0:15:31.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I initially heard it, I thought it was a rather absurd idea.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:31.03,0:15:36.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But according to Sawakiguchi, Hongou was apparently looking for a seventh actor.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:36.00,0:15:39.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With that bit of information, I'm certain that there was a seventh.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:39.17,0:15:43.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, Hongou wrote her script to keep the game fair.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:43.69,0:15:47.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't imagine her planning a mystery killer to suddenly appear out of nowhere.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:47.19,0:15:51.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Incidentally, there are a number of strange details in this video.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:51.38,0:15:53.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satoshi noted them down.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:54.77,0:15:57.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kounosu finds a floor map.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:57.22,0:15:58.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone illuminates it.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:58.38,0:16:00.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Presumably with a flashlight.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:00.77,0:16:02.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Another point.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:02.21,0:16:04.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone is looking for Kaitou.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:04.48,0:16:06.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The corridor is dark, and there's no light source.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:06.69,0:16:08.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone uses a flashlight.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:08.94,0:16:10.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A flashlight?
Dialogue: 9,0:16:10.63,0:16:12.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:12.05,0:16:15.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, none of the members had a flashlight.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:16.20,0:16:19.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you examine the scenes immediately following the use of the flashlight,
Dialogue: 9,0:16:19.14,0:16:21.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for example, the part where they enter the murder scene,
Dialogue: 9,0:16:21.99,0:16:23.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that fact should become apparent.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:24.33,0:16:29.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was certainly time for the holder to hide the flashlight, but there was no particular reason to.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:29.59,0:16:30.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know what you're thinking.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:30.95,0:16:33.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was just for lighting the scene, right?
Dialogue: 9,0:16:33.41,0:16:36.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But just keep this in mind for now.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:36.63,0:16:37.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And one more thing...
Dialogue: 9,0:16:37.71,0:16:41.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and this is from the perspective of a moviegoer, so don't take it the wrong way.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:41.22,0:16:43.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The movie is boring.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:43.47,0:16:44.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The acting is bad.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:44.69,0:16:47.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The camera work is completely amateur.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:48.47,0:16:51.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what if there were a reason behind that?
Dialogue: 9,0:16:51.90,0:16:57.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In this video, the cameraman was filming from the same perspective as the other characters.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:58.80,0:17:00.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you've figured it out by now.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:01.43,0:17:03.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't mean...
Dialogue: 9,0:17:04.50,0:17:07.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying that the cameraman was the seventh character?
Dialogue: 9,0:17:09.34,0:17:12.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There were seven from the start.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:12.31,0:17:18.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The six who were being filmed, and the one who was operating the camera.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:18.19,0:17:19.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Watch carefully.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:19.30,0:17:23.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here and there, you'll notice the actors looking right at the camera.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:24.25,0:17:27.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were indicating the fact that there was a cameraman there.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:27.83,0:17:30.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this point, the term "cameraman" is a bit inaccurate.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:30.49,0:17:32.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's use "seventh character".
Dialogue: 9,0:17:32.44,0:17:38.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now with this assumption in place, it's obvious who was operating the flashlight.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:38.24,0:17:43.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The bad camerawork, along with the fact that every scene is shot from only one perspective,
Dialogue: 9,0:17:43.66,0:17:46.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is explained by the fact that the camera was operated by one of the characters.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:46.83,0:17:49.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And here's the most important point:
Dialogue: 9,0:17:49.84,0:17:52.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When all the other characters left to find their respective rooms,
Dialogue: 9,0:17:52.44,0:17:55.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the camera was still filming until no one was left in the lobby.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:55.39,0:17:57.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then the scene fades to black.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:58.67,0:18:05.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the camera was left inactive in the lobby until the characters started returning.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:05.93,0:18:08.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Consequently, the crime is simple to explain.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:08.43,0:18:11.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The seventh character waited for everyone else to leave the lobby,
Dialogue: 9,0:18:11.92,0:18:16.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,stopped the camera, then took the master key from the office.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:17.45,0:18:24.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After killing Kaitou, he locked the door again, then waited in the lobby for everyone else to come back.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:27.28,0:18:29.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This concludes my deduction.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:29.65,0:18:36.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If Hongou hasn't already picked a seventh actor, then I suggest you find one quickly.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:36.56,0:18:37.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Two questions.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:37.84,0:18:45.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, isn't it unnatural to have an actor who doesn't speak, and who no one talks to?
Dialogue: 9,0:18:45.29,0:18:48.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hongou may have purposely done that to show motive.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:48.27,0:18:51.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This person was deliberately ignored by everyone else.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:51.75,0:18:56.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because of that, he couldn't say anything, either.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:56.31,0:19:03.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Second, if this were the case, then it wouldn't have taken long for the other characters to figure out who did it.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:03.06,0:19:06.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone would immediately suspect the sole member who was alone in the lobby.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:06.40,0:19:10.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, what you called the "second locked room" is still unsolved.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:10.38,0:19:14.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The seventh character's actions must have been obvious to all characters.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:14.80,0:19:18.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't everyone have figured out the culprit immediately?
Dialogue: 9,0:19:19.75,0:19:22.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the words of Sawakiguchi,
Dialogue: 9,0:19:22.26,0:19:24.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"That's not really important."
Dialogue: 9,0:19:25.99,0:19:29.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter if the characters on stage know exactly who did it.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:29.06,0:19:32.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it enough if it makes the viewers think about the mystery?
Dialogue: 9,0:19:33.27,0:19:36.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That may be exactly why there is no detective in this story.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:37.00,0:19:41.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was no reason to have anyone narrate their deductions because the culprit was obvious.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:55.38,0:19:56.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Congratulations.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:57.37,0:20:00.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems you have solved Hongou's puzzle.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:01.38,0:20:04.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your answer sounds like quite a stretch of the imagination,
Dialogue: 9,0:20:04.78,0:20:09.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but given that it fits all the facts, I have to agree that it is correct.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:10.50,0:20:12.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:12.48,0:20:14.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now we can complete the movie.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:21.20,0:20:23.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew I made the right choice.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:23.82,0:20:25.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have a gift.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:26.00,0:20:27.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A talent unique to you.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:29.15,0:20:31.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I, well...
Dialogue: 9,0:20:31.66,0:20:32.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm honored.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:33.24,0:20:36.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you christen the movie with a title?
Dialogue: 9,0:20:37.19,0:20:37.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A title?
Dialogue: 9,0:20:37.96,0:20:39.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anything that comes to mind.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:39.90,0:20:43.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think everyone will be happy with a title you come up with.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:46.51,0:20:48.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 9,0:20:48.23,0:20:50.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Going by the story...
Dialogue: 9,0:20:51.35,0:20:54.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about "What No One Noticed"?
Dialogue: 9,0:20:56.84,0:20:58.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a good title.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:58.37,0:20:59.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll go with that.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:10.65,0:21:12.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Home run.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:16.57,0:21:18.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All third years are to...
Dialogue: 9,0:21:18.71,0:21:21.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and so, with the cultural festival in October...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.60,0:21:34.43,Handwriting,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fsp01\blur0.5\an7\fs28\c&H6E6C71&\b0\pos(430.895,450.267)}There is a preview screening in the \NAudio Visual Classroom. \NI'm going to be there to see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.60,0:21:34.43,Handwriting,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.5\fs35\c&H6E6C71&\b1\pos(742.857,625.428)}Chitanda{\c&H6E6C71&\b0}
Dialogue: 9,0:21:34.43,0:21:38.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think any of us could have gone near that room.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:38.63,0:21:40.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. None of us...
Dialogue: 9,0:21:40.76,0:21:42.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...except you.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:42.49,0:21:43.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You did it?
Dialogue: 9,0:21:43.92,0:21:45.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you did it?
Dialogue: 9,0:21:45.45,0:21:46.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe it!
Dialogue: 9,0:21:47.23,0:21:48.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would you do that?
Dialogue: 9,0:21:48.70,0:21:49.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I wasn't expecting that!
Dialogue: 9,0:21:49.95,0:21:51.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait right there!
Dialogue: 9,0:21:51.22,0:21:51.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's getting away!
Dialogue: 9,0:21:51.58,0:21:53.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give it up!
Dialogue: 9,0:21:54.58,0:21:56.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}That was amazing!
Dialogue: 9,0:21:56.98,0:21:58.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Seriously! Hongou outdid herself this time.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:58.92,0:22:00.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the real Kaitou...
Dialogue: 9,0:22:00.80,0:22:02.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I never expected it to be the cameraman...
Dialogue: 9,0:22:01.43,0:22:02.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yo! I heard all about it.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:03.44,0:22:05.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently you figured it out for us?
Dialogue: 9,0:22:06.58,0:22:08.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I guess...
Dialogue: 9,0:22:08.26,0:22:10.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That twist was a shocker!
Dialogue: 9,0:22:10.85,0:22:12.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I liked it!
Dialogue: 9,0:22:12.22,0:22:13.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yo, Master Detective!
Dialogue: 9,0:22:14.47,0:22:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Master Detective?
Dialogue: 9,0:22:16.00,0:22:17.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Way to go!
Dialogue: 9,0:22:18.00,0:22:24.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\q2}Though, I was a bit disappointed that they didn't have the seventh\N character kill everyone in desperation after he was revealed.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:24.58,0:22:25.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right...
Dialogue: 9,0:22:25.54,0:22:27.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, thanks again!
Dialogue: 9,0:22:27.71,0:22:28.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Later!
Dialogue: 9,0:22:28.94,0:22:29.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right...
Dialogue: 9,0:22:30.37,0:22:32.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But still, Nakajou...
Dialogue: 9,0:22:32.08,0:22:32.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 9,0:22:33.06,0:22:34.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That twist was amazing.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:34.29,0:22:36.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{missing line}
Dialogue: 9,0:22:38.21,0:22:40.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess Haba wasn't happy with it.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:40.76,0:22:42.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Houtarou!
Dialogue: 9,0:22:42.50,0:22:43.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We saw it.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:43.44,0:22:44.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you think?
Dialogue: 9,0:22:45.05,0:22:45.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not bad.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:46.63,0:22:48.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I liked it.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:48.12,0:22:49.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't expecting the cameraman.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:49.97,0:22:53.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you already have this possibility in mind back then?
Dialogue: 9,0:22:53.45,0:22:55.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hadn't thought of this, no.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:56.08,0:22:56.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 9,0:22:57.75,0:23:00.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She didn't seemed too surprised...
Dialogue: 9,0:23:00.85,0:23:02.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, whatever.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:02.56,0:23:03.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-san...
Dialogue: 9,0:23:06.00,0:23:06.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 9,0:23:10.87,0:23:11.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe later!
Dialogue: 9,0:23:14.74,0:23:17.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, good job either way, Houtarou.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:17.50,0:23:18.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Empress was also happy with it.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:18.86,0:23:23.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The movie is complete, and I think everyone will enjoy the twist.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:26.76,0:23:27.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:28.69,0:23:30.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's something I want to ask you.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:30.42,0:23:30.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 9,0:23:31.92,0:23:33.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 9,0:23:33.65,0:23:36.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You came up with that solution, right?
Dialogue: 9,0:23:36.51,0:23:37.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:37.37,0:23:38.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All of it?
Dialogue: 9,0:23:38.21,0:23:38.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Probably.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:41.19,0:23:44.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So how do you explain what Haba-senpai said?
Dialogue: 9,0:23:44.67,0:23:45.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What Haba said?
Dialogue: 9,0:23:46.85,0:23:47.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know...
Dialogue: 9,0:23:51.78,0:23:55.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Throughout that whole movie, there was no mention of a rope anywhere. {RUH ROH}
